<div id="review_2312798240" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2312798240" />
    <a title="J.K. Grice" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72137025-j-k-grice"><img alt="J.K. Grice" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1507324623p2/72137025.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2312798240?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J.K. Grice" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J.K. Grice" href="/user/show/72137025-j-k-grice">J.K. Grice</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/72137025-j-k-grice?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2312798240" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12494347255297468133">&quot;The truth about what happens to us in this world keeps changing....it never stops.&quot;<br/><br/>I think this quote is a perfect summation for the theme of NIGHT FILM. This book is a great supernatural thriller that delves into the basic mystery of TRUTH: our constant pursuit of it, as well as the very thin curtain between truth &amp; reality, and memories &amp; perceptions of any given event or period in time. What do we actually KNOW to be the entire, factual truth about anything? Perceptions, assumptions, and rat</span>
  <span id="freeText12494347255297468133" style="display:none">"The truth about what happens to us in this world keeps changing....it never stops."<br /><br />I think this quote is a perfect summation for the theme of NIGHT FILM. This book is a great supernatural thriller that delves into the basic mystery of TRUTH: our constant pursuit of it, as well as the very thin curtain between truth &amp; reality, and memories &amp; perceptions of any given event or period in time. What do we actually KNOW to be the entire, factual truth about anything? Perceptions, assumptions, and rationalizations all serve to pepper our knowledge of the truth and perhaps riddle it with holes to boot. <br /><br />Marisha Pessl does such an impressive job in developing her characters and taking them on a journey into the unknown, with all kinds of plot twists along the way. I found this novel to be incredibly engaging and totally unpredictable. I love how the author weaves history, film making, and the occult throughout the telling of this fantastic tale. I also loved all of the documents, articles, and entries added throughout the book, as these gave the entire story such an expanded feeling of authenticity. NIGHT FILM reminded me a bit of another book dealing with some of the same subject matter, and that was Stephen Dobyn's <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15808328.The_Burn_Palace" title="The Burn Palace by Stephen Dobyns" rel="nofollow noopener">The Burn Palace</a>. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12494347255297468133" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


